Dragons don't take much interest in each other.
But I guess, if anything, size.
The larger a dragon, the older it is, and thus usually the more powerful and more desirable.
But, you know, dragons are just like people, they have their own individual interests.
They keep growing, but the growth is exponentially slower as they age.
The dragons of twokinds are shapeshifters, so obviously physical attraction is a bit meaningless.
They have a default size, which requires no energy to maintain. They can make themselves larger, but it takes more and more energy, so they can't stay big for long.
So a young dragon could pretend to be older, but it would be taxing, and they'd run out of energy pretty fast.
There are technically bigger dragons. There's some that specifically do nothing but work on making themselves big. Puff themselves up.
